                //its script is downloaded and evaluated. However, if web workers
                //are in play, the expectation is that a build has been done so
                //that only one script needs to be loaded anyway. This may need
                //to be reevaluated if other use cases become common.

                // Post a task to the event loop to work around a bug in WebKit
                // where the worker gets garbage-collected after calling
                // importScripts(): https://webkit.org/b/153317
                setTimeout(function() {}, 0);
                importScripts(url);

                //Account for anonymous modules
                context.completeLoad(moduleName);
            } catch (e) {
                context.onError(makeError('importscripts',
                                'importScripts failed for ' +
                                    moduleName + ' at ' + url,
                                e,
                                [moduleName]));
            }
        }
    };

    function getInteractiveScript() {
        if (interactiveScript && interactiveScript.readyState === 'interactive') {
            return interactiveScript;
        }

        eachReverse(scripts(), function (script) {
            if (script.readyState === 'interactive') {
                return (interactiveScript = script);
            }
        });
        return interactiveScript;
    }

    //Look for a data-main script attribute, which could also adjust the baseUrl.
    if (isBrowser && !cfg.skipDataMain) {
        //Figure out baseUrl. Get it from the script tag with require.js in it.
        eachReverse(scripts(), function (script) {
            //Set the 'head' where we can append children by
            //using the script's parent.
            if (!head) {
                head = script.parentNode;
            }

            //Look for a data-main attribute to set main script for the page
            //to load. If it is there, the path to data main becomes the
            //baseUrl, if it is not already set.
            dataMain = script.getAttribute('data-main');
            if (dataMain) {
                //Preserve dataMain in case it is a path (i.e. contains '?')
                mainScript = dataMain;

                //Set final baseUrl if there is not already an explicit one,
                //but only do so if the data-main value is not a loader plugin
                //module ID.
                if (!cfg.baseUrl && mainScript.indexOf('!') === -1) {
                    //Pull off the directory of data-main for use as the
                    //baseUrl.
                    src = mainScript.split('/');
                    mainScript = src.pop();
                    subPath = src.length ? src.join('/')  + '/' : './';

                    cfg.baseUrl = subPath;
                }

                //Strip off any trailing .js since mainScript is now
                //like a module name.
                mainScript = mainScript.replace(jsSuffixRegExp, '');

                //If mainScript is still a path, fall back to dataMain
                if (req.jsExtRegExp.test(mainScript)) {
                    mainScript = dataMain;
                }

                //Put the data-main script in the files to load.
                cfg.deps = cfg.deps ? cfg.deps.concat(mainScript) : [mainScript];

                return true;
            }
        });
    }

    /**
     * The function that handles definitions of modules. Differs from
     * require() in that a string for the module should be the first argument,
     * and the function to execute after dependencies are loaded should
     * return a value to define the module corresponding to the first argument's
     * name.
     */
    define = function (name, deps, callback) {
        var node, context;

        //Allow for anonymous modules
        if (typeof name !== 'string') {
            //Adjust args appropriately
            callback = deps;
            deps = name;
            name = null;
        }

        //This module may not have dependencies
        if (!isArray(deps)) {
            callback = deps;
            deps = null;
        }

        //If no name, and callback is a function, then figure out if it a
        //CommonJS thing with dependencies.
        if (!deps && isFunction(callback)) {
            deps = [];
            //Remove comments from the callback string,
            //look for require calls, and pull them into the dependencies,
            //but only if there are function args.
            if (callback.length) {
                callback
                    .toString()
                    .replace(commentRegExp, commentReplace)
                    .replace(cjsRequireRegExp, function (match, dep) {
                        deps.push(dep);
                    });

                //May be a CommonJS thing even without require calls, but still
                //could use exports, and module. Avoid doing exports and module
                //work though if it just needs require.
                //REQUIRES the function to expect the CommonJS variables in the
                //order listed below.
                deps = (callback.length === 1 ? ['require'] : ['require', 'exports', 'module']).concat(deps);
            }
        }

        //If in IE 6-8 and hit an anonymous define() call, do the interactive
        //work.
        if (useInteractive) {
            node = currentlyAddingScript || getInteractiveScript();
            if (node) {
                if (!name) {
                    name = node.getAttribute('data-requiremodule');
                }
                context = contexts[node.getAttribute('data-requirecontext')];
            }
        }

        //Always save off evaluating the def call until the script onload handler.
        //This allows multiple modules to be in a file without prematurely
        //tracing dependencies, and allows for anonymous module support,
        //where the module name is not known until the script onload event
        //occurs. If no context, use the global queue, and get it processed
        //in the onscript load callback.
        if (context) {
            context.defQueue.push([name, deps, callback]);
            context.defQueueMap[name] = true;
        } else {
            globalDefQueue.push([name, deps, callback]);
        }
    };

    define.amd = {
        jQuery: true
    };

    /**
     * Executes the text. Normally just uses eval, but can be modified
     * to use a better, environment-specific call. Only used for transpiling
     * loader plugins, not for plain JS modules.
     * @param {String} text the text to execute/evaluate.
     */
    req.exec = function (text) {
        /*jslint evil: true */
        return eval(text);
    };

    //Set up with config info.
    req(cfg);
}(this, (typeof setTimeout === 'undefined' ? undefined : setTimeout)));

		//# sourceURL=requirejs.min.js
	</script>
	<script type="application/javascript" nonce="5f00a4486f4b04ed7940da9bd7aa2058" crossorigin="anonymous">
		require.config({
			baseUrl: '//img.imgsmail.ru',
			bundles: {
        		'react.env': ['react', 'react-dom', 'react-intl']
    		},
			waitSeconds: 0,
			onNodeCreated: function (node, config, moduleName, url) {
				node.setAttribute('crossorigin', 'anonymous');
			},
			deps: ['//img.imgsmail.ru/pkgs/login.mail.ru/22914/ru_RU/polyfills.js']
		});

		require.onError = function (err) {
			window.coreLogger && coreLogger.dispatchError(err, null, {category: 'requirejs'});
		};
		//# sourceURL=requirejs-config.js
	</script>

		<!-- –ò–Ω–ª–∞–π–Ω–∏–º shazam –∏ –∫–æ–Ω—Ñ–∏–≥—É—Ä–∏—Ä—É–µ–º –µ–≥–æ -->
	<script type="application/javascript" id="shazam" nonce="5f00a4486f4b04ed7940da9bd7aa2058" crossorigin="anonymous">
		 var shazam = function (options) {
	// –†–µ–≥—É–ª—è—Ä–Ω–æ–µ –≤—ã—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∏–µ –¥–ª—è –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–∏ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞
	var R_VERSION_REG_EXP = /^(\d+)(?:\.(\d+)(?:\.(\d+)(?:-(.+?)\.(\d+))?)?)?$/i;

	// –ö–æ–Ω—Å—Ç–∞–Ω—Ç—ã, –æ—Ç–∫—É–¥–∞ –±–µ—Ä–µ—Ç—Å—è —Ä–µ–ª–∏–∑ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞
	var P_VERSION = {
		SEMVER: 'semver',
		BRANCH: 'branch'
	};

	// –ö–æ–Ω—Å—Ç–∞–Ω—Ç—ã –æ–∫—Ä—É–∂–µ–Ω–∏—è
	var ENV = {
		PROD: 'production',
		DEV: 'development'
	};

	// –°–ø–∏—Å–æ–∫ –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–π —Ä–µ–ª–∏–∑–∞ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞
	var R_VERSIONS = [
		'major',
		'minor',
		'patch',
		'pre',
		'build'
	];

	/**
	 * –ö–æ–Ω—Å—Ç—Ä—É–∫—Ç–æ—Ä –æ—à–∏–±–∫–∏
	 * @param str {String} —Ç–µ–∫—Å—Ç
	 * @return {Error} –æ—à–∏–±–∫–∞
	 */
	function makeError (str) {
		return new Error("[kapellmeister-ssi] Failed to " + str);
	}

	/**
	 * –†–µ–∫—É—Ä—Å–∏–≤–Ω–æ –∫–æ–ø–∏—Ä—É–µ—Ç –æ–¥–∏–Ω –æ–±—ä–µ–∫—Ç –≤ –¥—Ä—É–≥–æ–π,
	 * —á—Ç–æ –±—ã –∏–∑–±–µ–∂–∞—Ç—å —Å–æ—Ö—Ä–∞–Ω–µ–Ω–∏–µ —Å—Å—ã–ª–æ–∫ –Ω–∞ –∏—Å—Ö–æ–¥–Ω—ã–π –æ–±—ä–µ–∫—Ç
	 * @param from {Object} –æ—Ç–∫—É–¥–∞ –∫–æ–ø–∏—Ä—É–µ–º
	 * @param to {Object} –∫—É–¥–∞ –∫–æ–ø–∏—Ä—É–µ–º
	 */
	function deepObjCopy (from, to) {
		for (var key in from) {
			if (typeof from[key] !== 'object') {
				to[key] = from[key];
			} else {
				to[key] = Object.create(null);

				deepObjCopy(from[key], to[key]);
			}
		}
	}

	/**
	 * –ü–æ–ª—É—á–∞–µ—Ç —Ç–∏–ø —Ä–µ–ª–∏–∑–∞ –∏–∑ —Å—Ç—Ä–æ–∫–∏ —Å –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–µ–π
	 * @param str {String} –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—è
	 * @return {VersionData} –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—è –∏ —Ç–∏–ø —Ä–µ–ª–∏–∑–∞
	 */
	function parseVersionString (str) {
		var match = str.match(R_VERSION_REG_EXP);

		var result = {
			version: str,
			type: match ? P_VERSION.SEMVER : P_VERSION.BRANCH
		};

		if (match) {
			R_VERSIONS.forEach(function (attr, index) {
				result[attr] = match[index + 1];
			});
		}

		return result;
	};

	/**
	 * –°—Ä–∞–≤–Ω–∏–≤–∞–µ—Ç –¥–∞–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–π –ø–æ –∫–ª—é—á—É
	 * @param v1 {VersionData} –¥–∞–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –æ –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–∏ 1
	 * @param v2 {VersionData} –¥–∞–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –æ –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–∏ 2
	 * @param attrName {String} –∫–ª—é—á –¥–ª—è —Å—Ä–∞–≤–Ω–µ–Ω–∏—è
	 * @return {VersionData|Boolean}
	 */
	function compareVersionAttribute (v1, v2, attrName) {
		if (v1[attrName] === v2[attrName]) {
			return false;
		}

		return (Number(v1[attrName]) > Number(v2[attrName])) ? v1 : v2;
	}

	/**
	 * –í—ã–±–∏—Ä–∞–µ—Ç –∏—Å–ø–æ–ª—å–∑—É–µ–º—É—é –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—é –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–æ–≤
	 * @param lv {String} –ª–æ–∫–∞–ª—å–Ω–∞—è –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—è –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞
	 * @param rv {String} —É–¥–∞–ª–µ–Ω–Ω—ã—è –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—è –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞
	 * @param env {String} –∑–Ω–∞—á–µ–Ω–∏–µ –æ–∫—Ä—É–∂–µ–Ω–∏—è
	 * @return {VersionData}
	 */
	function compareVersions (lv, rv, env) {
		var lvData = parseVersionString(lv);
		var rvData = parseVersionString(rv);

		if (env === ENV.DEV) {
			if (lvData.type === P_VERSION.BRANCH) {
				return lvData;
			}

			if (rvData.type === P_VERSION.BRANCH) {
				return rvData;
			}
		}

		if ((lvData.type !== P_VERSION.SEMVER) || (rvData.type !== P_VERSION.SEMVER)) {
			throw makeError("compare " + lvData.version + " and " + rvData.version + " versions due their types");
		}

		var versionData = lvData;

		R_VERSIONS.some(function(attr) {
			var compared = compareVersionAttribute(lvData, rvData, attr);

			if (attr === 'pre' && compared) {
				throw makeError("compare " + lvData.version + " and " + rvData.version + " versions due their inconsistency");
			}

			if (compared) {
				versionData = compared;
			}

			return compared;
		});

		return versionData;
	}

	/**
	 * –°—Ç—Ä–æ–∏—Ç url –¥–æ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞, –∏—Å–ø–æ–ª—å–∑—É–µ–º—ã–π RequireJS
	 * @param hb {boolean} —Ç–∏–ø –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞ (hotbox –∏–ª–∏ risk)
	 * @param options {Object} –ø–∞—Ä–∞–º–µ—Ç—Ä—ã c —É—Ä–ª–∞–º–∏
	 * @param prod {boolean} prod –∏–ª–∏ dev –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç
	 * @return {String}
	 */
	function getPackageUrl(hb, options, prod) {
		switch (true) {
			case prod && hb:
				return options.url.hbProd;
			case prod && !hb:
				return options.url.prod;
			case !prod && hb:
				return options.url.hbDev;
			case !prod && !hb:
				return options.url.dev;
		}
	}

	/**
	 * –°—Ç—Ä–æ–∏—Ç url, –∏—Å–ø–æ–ª—å–∑—É–µ–º—ã–π RequireJS, –¥–æ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞
	 * @param name {String} –Ω–∞–∑–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞
	 * @param versionData {VersionData} –¥–∞–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–∏ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞
	 * @param packageData {Object} –æ–±—â–∏–µ –¥–∞–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞
	 * @param options {Object} –ø—Ä–æ—á–∏–µ –ø–∞—Ä–∞–º–µ—Ç—Ä—ã
	 * @return {String}
	 */
	function getUrl(name, versionData, packageData, options) {
		var version = versionData.version;
		var path = packageData.path || '/index';
		var lang = '';

		// –ü–∞–∫–µ—Ç –±–µ—Ä–µ—Ç—Å—è –ø–æ —Å–∏–º-–ª–∏–Ω–∫—É:
		if (options.isDev && options.isLocal) {
			return (options.url.local || './node_modules/') + name + path;
		}

		// –ü–∞–∫–µ—Ç –±–µ—Ä–µ—Ç—Å—è –∏–∑ –≤–µ—Ç–∫–∏:
		var isFromBranchPackage = versionData.type === P_VERSION.BRANCH && options.isDev;
		// –ü–∞–∫–µ—Ç –∏–∑ hotbox (–∏–Ω–∞—á–µ ‚Äî risk)
		var hb = packageData.hb || false;

		// –ù—É–∂–Ω–∞ –ª–æ–∫–∞–ª–∏–∑–∞—Ü–∏—è
		if (options.hasLang && options.lang && !isFromBranchPackage) {
			lang = '/' + options.lang;
		}

		return getPackageUrl(hb, options, !isFromBranchPackage) + '/' + name + '/' + version + lang + path;
	}

	function init(options) {
		// –°–æ–¥–µ—Ä–∂–∏–º–æ–µ kapellmeister.json
        // –ù–µ—Ç —É–¥–∞–ª–µ–Ω–Ω–æ–≥–æ –∫–æ–Ω—Ñ–∏–≥–∞ - –∏—Å–ø–æ–ª—å–∑—É–µ–º –ª–æ–∫–∞–ª—å–Ω—ã–π
		var remote = options.remote || {};
		// –°–æ–¥–µ—Ä–∂–∏–º–æ–µ –ø–æ –∫–ª—é—á—É kapellmeister –∏–∑ package.json
		var local = options.local;
		// –£—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–∞–≤–ª–∏–≤–∞–µ—Ç—Å—è –ø–µ—Ä–µ–¥ –≤—ã–∑–æ–≤–æ–º –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞:
		var appName = options.appName || 'e.mail.ru';
		var configLang = local.lang || remote.lang || options.lang || 'ru_RU';
		var env = options.env || ENV.PROD;
		// –°–æ—Ö—Ä–∞–Ω—è–µ–º —Å—Å—ã–ª–∫–∏ –Ω–∞ –æ–±—ä–µ–∫—Ç—ã —Å –Ω–∞—Å—Ç—Ä–æ–π–∫–∞–º–∏ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–æ–≤
		var remotePackages = remote.packages || {};
		var localPackages = local.packages;
		// –°–æ—Ö—Ä–∞–Ω—è–µ–º —Å—Å—ã–ª–∫—É –Ω–∞ default –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–∏ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–æ–≤
		var versions = remote.versions && remote.versions.default || {};

		if (remote.env === ENV.DEV) {
			env = remote.env;
		}

		// –ö–æ–ø–∏—Ä—É–µ–º –≤ –æ–±—â–∏–π –æ–±—ä–µ–∫—Ç —Å –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—è–º–∏, –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–∏ –∏—Å–ø–æ–ª—å–∑—É–µ–º—ã–µ
		// –ø—Ä–æ–µ–∫—Ç–æ–º —Å–æ–≥–ª–∞—Å–Ω–æ kapellmeister.json (–µ—Å–ª–∏ –æ–Ω –µ—Å—Ç—å)
        if (remote.versions && remote.versions.projects[appName]) {
            deepObjCopy(remote.versions.projects[appName], versions);
        }

		// –î–æ–±–∞–≤–ª—è–µ–º –Ω–∞–∑–≤–∞–Ω–∏—è –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–æ–≤, –∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä—ã–µ —É–∫–∞–∑–∞–Ω—ã —Ç–æ–ª—å–∫–æ –≤ —Å–∞–º–æ–º –ø—Ä–æ–µ–∫—Ç–µ
		Object.keys(local.versions.local).forEach(function (name) {
			if (!versions[name]) {
				versions[name] = null;
			}
		});

		// –ò—Ç–µ—Ä–∏—Ä—É–µ–º—Å—è —É–∂–µ –ø–æ –ø–æ–ª–Ω–æ–º—É —Å–ø–∏—Å–∫—É –Ω–∞–∑–≤–∞–Ω–∏–π –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–æ–≤
		Object.keys(versions).forEach(function (name) {
			// –í–µ—Ä—Å–∏—è —Å–æ–≥–ª–∞—Å–Ω–æ kapellmeister.json
			var remoteVersion = versions[name];
			// –í–µ—Ä—Å–∏—è —Å–æ–≥–ª–∞—Å–Ω–æ package.json
			var localVersion = local.versions.local[name];
			// –î–∞–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞ —Å–æ–≥–ª–∞—Å–Ω–æ –ø—Ä–∏–æ—Ä–∏—Ç–µ—Ç—É
			var packageData = localPackages[name] || remotePackages[name] || {};

			// –û–±—â–∏–µ –¥–∞–Ω–Ω—ã–µ, –Ω–µ–æ–±—Ö–æ–¥–∏–º—ã–µ –¥–ª—è —Ñ–æ—Ä–º–∏—Ä–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏—è url –¥–æ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞
			var urlOptions = {
				// –û–∫—Ä—É–∂–µ–Ω–∏–µ —Ä–∞–∑—Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–∫–∏
				isDev: env === ENV.DEV,
				// –ù—É–∂–µ–Ω –ø–µ—Ä–µ–≤–æ–¥
				hasLang: packageData.i18n && configLang,
				// –ü–∞–∫–µ—Ç –±–µ—Ä–µ—Ç—Å—è –ø–æ —Å–∏–º-–ª–∏–Ω–∫—É –ª–æ–∫–∞–ª—å–Ω–æ
				isLocal: packageData.local,
				// –ù–∞–±–æ—Ä url –¥–ª—è –≤—Å–µ—Ö —Ç–∏–ø–æ–≤ —Ä–∞–∑—Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–∫–∏
				url: options.url,
				// –Ø–∑—ã–∫ –ø–æ-—É–º–æ–ª—á–∞–Ω–∏—é
				lang: configLang
			};

			var versionData = null;

			// –ù–µ—Ç –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–∏ –≤ package.json - –±–µ—Ä–µ–º –∏–∑ kapellmeister.json
			if (!localVersion) {
				versionData = parseVersionString(remoteVersion);
			// –ù–µ—Ç –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–∏ –≤ kapellmeister.json - –±–µ—Ä–µ–º –∏–∑ package.json
			} else if (!remoteVersion && localVersion) {
				versionData = parseVersionString(localVersion);
			// –ï—Å—Ç—å –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–∏ –∏ —Ç–∞–º –∏ —Ç–∞–º - —Å—Ä–∞–≤–Ω–∏–≤–∞–µ–º
			} else {
				versionData = compareVersions(localVersion, remoteVersion, env);
			}

			// –ü–µ—Ä–µ–∑–∞–ø–∏—Å—ã–≤–∞–µ–º –≤ –æ–±—ä–µ–∫—Ç–µ —Å –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—è–º–∏ –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏—é –Ω–∞ url –¥–æ –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç–∞
			versions[name] = getUrl(name, versionData, packageData, urlOptions);
		});

		return versions;
	}

	if (typeof window !== 'undefined' && window.require) {
		window.require.config({ paths: init(options) });
	} else {
		throw makeError('detect RequireJS instance in window');
	}
};

		//# sourceURL=shazam.min.js
	</script>

	<script type="application/javascript" nonce="5f00a4486f4b04ed7940da9bd7aa2058" crossorigin="anonymous">
		var shazamEnv = 'production';
		shazam({
			appName: 'login.mail.ru',
			local: KAPELLMEISTER_LOCAL,
			remote: KAPELLMEISTER_REMOTE,
			url: {
				dev: '/pkgs',
				prod: '//img.imgsmail.ru/pkgs',
				local: './node_modules/',
				hbProd: '//img.imgsmail.ru/hb/e.mail.ru',
				hbDev: '//static.mail.cloud.devmail.ru/omega',
			},
			env: shazamEnv,
			lang: 'ru_RU',
		});
		//# sourceURL=shazam-config.js
	</script>
	<div id="login-content">
		<div class="page-headline" data-is-mobile-app="false">

<script>
	var xray = {
		send: function (t, data) {
			var src = '//xray.mail.ru/update?p=light&t=' + encodeURIComponent(t);

			if (data) {
				var iItems = data.i;
				if (iItems) {
					if (typeof iItems === 'string') {
						iItems = [iItems];
					}

					var iItemsParts = [];

					if (Object.prototype.toString.call(iItems) === '[object Array]') {
						for (var i = iItems.length; i--;) {
							iItemsParts.push(encodeURIComponent(iItems[i]) + ':1');
						}
					} else {
						for (var key in iItems) {
							iItemsParts.push(encodeURIComponent(key) + ':' + encodeURIComponent(iItems[key]));
						}
					}

					src += '&i=' + iItemsParts.join(',');
				}

				try {
					if (data.rlog_message) {
						src += '&rlog_message=' + encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(data.rlog_message));
					}

					if (data.rlog) {
						src += '&rlog=' + encodeURIComponent(data.rlog);
					}
				} catch (e) {
				}
			}

			src += '&v=1&email=test_nt_1@mail.ru&rnd=' + Math.random();

			(new Image()).src = src;
		}
	};
</script>

	(function (w, d) {

			try {
				m$portal.cookie('browser_warning_hide', 1, {expires: 365, path: '/'});
			} catch (e) {

				i: 'needmodernbrowser_close'
			});
		};
	})(window, document);

<script>
	(function (w, d) {
		var close = d.getElementById('announcements__compatibility-mode__infomessage__close');
		close.onclick = function () {
			try {
				m$portal.cookie('browser_iecm_hide', 1, {expires: 365, path: '/'});
			} catch (e) {
			}

			new Image().src = '//rs.mail.ru/sb5825351.gif?' + Math.random();

			setTimeout(function () {
				location.reload();
			}, 100);

			xray.send('ann', {
				i: 'compatibility-mode_close'
			});
		};
	})(window, document);
</script>


<script type="text/javascript">
	(function (w, d, ua) {
		try {
			var
				mail_cookie = m$portal.S_Cookie('mail')
				, blocks = {
					'allowed-full-version': {
						el: d.getElementById('announcements__allowed-full-version')
					}
					, 'needmodernbrowser': {
						el: d.getElementById('announcements__needmodernbrowser')
						, closed: m$portal.cookie('browser_warning_hide')
					}
					, 'compatibility-mode': {
						el: d.getElementById('announcements__compatibility-mode')
						, closed: m$portal.cookie('browser_iecm_hide')
					}
				}
				, can_use_full_version = true
				, compatibility_mode = /\bMSIE\s[67]/.test(ua) && /\bTrident/.test(ua)
				, light = mail_cookie.getLocal('light')
			;

			

			if (light) {
				if (can_use_full_version) {
					blocks['allowed-full-version'].el.style.display = '';
					new Image().src = '//rs.mail.ru/d3950576.gif?' + Math.random();
					new Image().src = '//mail.radar.imgsmail.ru/update?email=test_nt_1@mail.ru&p=mail&t=lite_afv_an&v=1&rlog=lite_afv_an&rlog_message=' + encodeURIComponent('ua=' + ua) + '&rnd=' + Math.random();

					xray.send('ann', {
						i: 'allowed-full-version'
					});
				} else {
					if (compatibility_mode) {
						if (!blocks['compatibility-mode'].closed) {
							blocks['compatibility-mode'].el.style.display = '';
							new Image().src = '//rs.mail.ru/d5825351.gif?' + Math.random();

							xray.send('ann', {
								i: 'compatibility-mode'
							});
						}
					} else {
						if (!blocks['needmodernbrowser'].closed) {
							blocks['needmodernbrowser'].el.style.display = '';
							new Image().src = '//rs.mail.ru/d3950567.gif?' + Math.random();

							xray.send('ann', {
								i: 'needmodernbrowser'
							});
						}
					}
				}
			}
		} catch (e) {
		}
	})(window, document, navigator.userAgent);
</script>

			<script>
				var $selectAllWrapper = document.getElementById('SelectAllWrapper');
				if ($selectAllWrapper) {
					// —É–¥–∞–ª—è–µ–º –∫–ª–∞—Å—Å nojsdn
					$selectAllWrapper.className = 'toolbar__buttons';
				}

				function toggleCheckboxes(el) {
					var state = el.checked,
						$checkboxes = document.getElementById('MessageList').getElementsByTagName('input');

						if ($checkboxes) {
							for (var i = 0; i < $checkboxes.length; i++) {
								if ($checkboxes[i].type === 'checkbox') {
									$checkboxes[i].checked = state;
								}
							}
						}

						return true;
				}
			</script>

<script type="text/javascript" >
try {
    (function(global, name, url) {
        url = url || '//r3.mail.ru/j/';
        var yaads = global[name] || [];
        global.yaads_rb_logs = global.yaads_rb_logs || {};
        function get_charmap() {
            var exceptions = [34, 35, 37, 47, 60, 62, 63, 75, 91, 92, 93, 94, 96, 107, 123, 124, 125];
            var charmap = {
                46: 33, //. => !
                45: 36, //- => $
                32: 40 //  => (
            }
            var fbc = [38, 39, 43, 61, 126];
            /*["&", "'", "+", "=", "~"] - some browsers uses percent-encoding for this symbols, but we stil can use it in charmap for any rare thing. NB! ~ (126) is used as field separator*/

            var not_avaliable = exceptions.concat(fbc);
            for (var k in charmap) {
                not_avaliable.push(charmap[k]);
            }

            var code = 33;

            function get_code() {
                while (code < 127 && not_avaliable.indexOf(code) >= 0) {
                    code += 1;
                }
                return code++;
            }

            var ranges = [
                [48, 58], // - digits
                [97, 123], // - latin
                [1072, 1104], // - russian
                [1105, 1106] // russian "—ë"
            ];

            for (var i = 0; i < ranges.length; i++) {
                var s = ranges[i][0],
                    f = ranges[i][1];
                while (s < f) {
                    charmap[s] = get_code();
                    if (!charmap[s]) throw new Error('can\'t encode character ' + String.fromCharCode(s) + '(' + s + ')');
                    s++;
                }
            }
            return charmap;
        }
        function encodeStr(str, charmap) {
            var unknown = 32;
            var replacements = [
                [/\s/g, ' ']
            ];
            str = str.toLowerCase();
            for (var i = 0; i < replacements.length; i++) {
                str = str.replace.apply(str, replacements[i]);
            }
            var coded = [];
            for (var i = 0, l = str.length; i < l; i++) {
                var c = str.charCodeAt(i);
                c = charmap[c] ? charmap[c] : charmap[unknown];
                coded[i] = String.fromCharCode(c);
            }
            return coded.join('');
        }
        function getUrlLogItem(data) {
            var charmap = get_charmap();
            var title = data.assets.filter(function(ob) {
                return ob.title;
            }).pop();
            title = title && title.title && title.title.value || '';
            var text = data.assets.filter(function(ob) {
                return ob.data && ob.ext && ob.ext.type === 2;
            }).pop();
            text = text && text.data && text.data.value || '';
            var domain = data.assets.filter(function(ob) {
                return ob.data && ob.ext && ob.ext.type === 11;
            }).pop();
            domain = domain && domain.data.value || '';
            if (!title || !text || !domain) {
                return '';
            }
            return [encodeStr(domain, charmap), encodeStr(title, charmap), encodeStr(text, charmap)].join(String.fromCharCode('126'));
        }
        function setLogs(data, newAdIds) {
            var adItems = [];
            for (var a = 0; a < data.adIds.length; a++) {
                if (newAdIds.indexOf(data.adIds[a]) !== -1) {
                    adItems.push(data.bid[a]);
                }
            }
            var bound = (2083 - url.length);
            var l = 0;
            var ind = 0;
            var ads = [];
            while (ind < adItems.length && l < bound) {
                var adItem = adItems[ind];
                var itemData = adItem.adm.native;
                /*if (!!itemData.adType || adItems.length === 1) {*/
                    // —É –µ–¥–∏–Ω—Å—Ç–≤–µ–Ω–Ω–æ–≥–æ –≤ –º–∞—Å—Å–∏–≤–µ –Ω–µ—Ç adType, –Ω–æ —É–∂–µ –æ—Ç—Å–µ—è–ª–∏ –≤—ã—à–µ –ø–æ adIds
                    var str = getUrlLogItem(itemData);

                    l += str.length;
                    if (l > bound) break;
                    if (!!str) {
                        ads.push(str);
                    }
                /*}*/
                ind++;
            }
            // console.log(url + ads.join('/'));
            new Image().src = url + ads.join('/');
        }

        Object.defineProperty(window, 'yaads', {
            get: function() { return yaads; },
            set: function(newYaads) {
                if (newYaads.callSuccessCb) {
                    var oldCS = newYaads.callSuccessCb;
                    newYaads.callSuccessCb = function(t) {
                        // console.log('Render data', t);
                        var seatbidData = t.data.seatbid;
                        var idInLogs = global.yaads_rb_logs.hasOwnProperty(t.id);
                        var globalItemadIds = idInLogs ? global.yaads_rb_logs[t.id].adIds : [];
                        var newAdsIds = [];
                        var adIds = seatbidData[0].adIds;
                        if (adIds && adIds.length) {
                            for (var arrInd = 0; arrInd < adIds.length; arrInd++) {
                                if (globalItemadIds.indexOf(adIds[arrInd]) === -1) {
                                    newAdsIds.push(adIds[arrInd]);
                                }
                            }
                        }

                        if (!!newAdsIds.length) {
                            setLogs(seatbidData[0], newAdsIds);
                            if (!idInLogs) {
                                global.yaads_rb_logs[t.id] = {};
                            }
                            global.yaads_rb_logs[t.id]['id'] = t.id;
                            global.yaads_rb_logs[t.id]['adIds'] = globalItemadIds.concat(newAdsIds);
                        }
                        oldCS.call(newYaads, t);
                    }
                }
                yaads = newYaads;
                // console.log('Try set yaads:', newYaads)
            },
            enumerable: true,
            configurable: true
        });
    })(this, "yaads");

} catch (e) {
    try {
        // console.log('//r3.mail.ru/j/error/' + e.message);

    } catch (e) {}
}

}\\n<\\/style>\\n    <script>\\n    (function(params) {\\n        var closeEl, closeBubbleEl, closeItemsEl, closeWrapEl, closeOverEl;\\n        var pixels = {\\n            ni: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635784.gif?\\",\\n            ab: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635789.gif?\\",\\n            sp: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635790.gif?\\",\\n            cv: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635791.gif?\\"\\n        };\\n        function stopE(e) {\\n            if (e) { e.preventDefault(); e.stopImmediatePropagation(); }\\n        }\\n        function addElemEvent(E, eventName, callback) {\\n            E.addEventListener ? E.addEventListener(eventName, callback, !1) : E.attachEvent && E.attachEvent(\\"on\\" + eventName, callback);\\n        }\\n        function removeElemEvent(E, eventName, callback) {\\n            E.removeEventListener ? E.removeEventListener(eventName, callback, !1) : E.detachEvent && E.detachEvent(\\"on\\" + eventName, callback);\\n        }\\n        function dispatchEvent(el, type) {\\n            var evt;\\n            if (typeof window.CustomEvent === 'function') {\\n                evt = new CustomEvent(type, {\\n                    bubbles: true\\n                });\\n            } else {\\n                evt = document.createEvent('CustomEvent');\\n                evt.initCustomEvent(type, true, false, null);\\n            }\\n            el.dispatchEvent(evt);\\n        }\\n        function sendPix(pix, params) {\\n            var img = document.createElement('img');\\n            img.src = pix || '';\\n            img.style.display = 'none';\\n            params.closeWrapEl.appendChild(img);\\n        }\\n        function getParentBannerItem(el) {\\n            var retval = null;\\n            var parentAttr = 'data-closewrap-container';\\n            var parentEl = el;\\n            while (parentEl) {\\n                if (parentEl === document.getElementsByTagName('body')[0]) {\\n                    retval = null;\\n                    break;\\n                } else if (parentEl.getAttribute(parentAttr)) {\\n                    retval = parentEl;\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n                parentEl = parentEl.parentElement;\\n            }\\n            return retval;\\n        }\\n        function getParentBannerSlot(el) {\\n            var slotClassName = 'mrg-tag';\\n            var slotEl = el;\\n            if (typeof el.closest === 'function') {\\n                return el.closest('.' + slotClassName);\\n            }\\n            while (slotEl !== null) {\\n                if (slotEl.className.indexOf(slotClassName) !== -1) {\\n                    return slotEl;\\n                }\\n                slotEl = slotEl.parentElement;\\n            }\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n        function closeAll(params) {\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className = params.closeWrapEl.className.replace(' _active', ' _hidden');\\n            removeElemEvent(params.closeEl, 'click', onCloseClick);\\n            removeElemEvent(params.closeOverEl, 'click', hideClose);\\n            for (var i = 0; i < params.closeItemsEl.length; i++) {\\n                removeElemEvent(params.closeItemsEl[i], 'click', onCloseReasonClick);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        function onCloseReasonClick(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            var pix = pixels[e.currentTarget.getAttribute('data-reason')];\\n            if (pix) { sendPix(pix, params); }\\n            sendPix(params.closeEl.getAttribute('data-closepix'), params);\\n            closeAll(params);\\n            \\/* dispatch close event to RbExt *\\/\\n            var parentBannerSlotItem = getParentBannerSlot(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            if (parentBannerSlotItem) {\\n                dispatchEvent(parentBannerSlotItem, 'mrg-close');\\n            }\\n        }\\n        function onCloseClick(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            if (params.closeWrapEl.className.indexOf(' _active') === -1) { showClose(params); } else { hideClose(params); }\\n        }\\n        function hideClose(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className = params.closeWrapEl.className.replace(' _active', '');\\n            var parentBannerWrapItem = getParentBannerItem(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            parentBannerWrapItem.className = parentBannerWrapItem.className.replace(' _close-overlay', '');\\n        }\\n        function showClose(params) {\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className += ' _active';\\n            var parentBannerWrapItem = getParentBannerItem(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            parentBannerWrapItem.className += ' _close-overlay';\\n        }\\n        function init() {\\n            if (!params || !params.rootId || !document.querySelectorAll) return;\\n            var rootElem = document.getElementById(params.rootId);\\n            if (!rootElem) return;\\n            closeWrapEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-cross-wrap');\\n            if (!closeWrapEl || !closeWrapEl[0]) return;\\n            closeEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-cross');\\n            closeBubbleEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-cross-bubble');\\n            closeOverEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-overlay');\\n            for (var k = 0; k < closeEl.length; k++) {\\n                closeItemsEl = closeWrapEl[k].querySelectorAll('.js-close-reason');\\n                if (!closeEl || !closeBubbleEl || !closeOverEl || !closeWrapEl[k] || !closeEl[k] || !closeBubbleEl[k] || !closeOverEl[k]) return;\\n                addElemEvent(closeBubbleEl[k], 'click', function(e) {\\n                    e.stopImmediatePropagation();\\n                    e.preventDefault();\\n                });\\n                addElemEvent(closeEl[k], 'click', onCloseClick.bind(null, {\\n                    closeWrapEl:closeWrapEl[k],\\n }\\n<\\/style>\\n    <script>\\n    (function(params) {\\n        var closeEl, closeBubbleEl, closeItemsEl, closeWrapEl, closeOverEl;\\n        var pixels = {\\n            ni: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635784.gif?\\",\\n            ab: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635789.gif?\\",\\n            sp: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635790.gif?\\",\\n            cv: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635791.gif?\\"\\n        };\\n        function stopE(e) {\\n            if (e) { e.preventDefault(); e.stopImmediatePropagation(); }\\n        }\\n        function addElemEvent(E, eventName, callback) {\\n            E.addEventListener ? E.addEventListener(eventName, callback, !1) : E.attachEvent && E.attachEvent(\\"on\\" + eventName, callback);\\n        }\\n        function removeElemEvent(E, eventName, callback) {\\n            E.removeEventListener ? E.removeEventListener(eventName, callback, !1) : E.detachEvent && E.detachEvent(\\"on\\" + eventName, callback);\\n        }\\n        function dispatchEvent(el, type) {\\n            var evt;\\n            if (typeof window.CustomEvent === 'function') {\\n                evt = new CustomEvent(type, {\\n                    bubbles: true\\n                });\\n            } else {\\n                evt = document.createEvent('CustomEvent');\\n                evt.initCustomEvent(type, true, false, null);\\n            }\\n            el.dispatchEvent(evt);\\n        }\\n        function sendPix(pix, params) {\\n            var img = document.createElement('img');\\n            img.src = pix || '';\\n            img.style.display = 'none';\\n            params.closeWrapEl.appendChild(img);\\n        }\\n        function getParentBannerItem(el) {\\n            var retval = null;\\n            var parentAttr = 'data-closewrap-container';\\n            var parentEl = el;\\n            while (parentEl) {\\n                if (parentEl === document.getElementsByTagName('body')[0]) {\\n                    retval = null;\\n                    break;\\n                } else if (parentEl.getAttribute(parentAttr)) {\\n                    retval = parentEl;\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n                parentEl = parentEl.parentElement;\\n            }\\n            return retval;\\n        }\\n        function getParentBannerSlot(el) {\\n            var slotClassName = 'mrg-tag';\\n            var slotEl = el;\\n            if (typeof el.closest === 'function') {\\n                return el.closest('.' + slotClassName);\\n            }\\n            while (slotEl !== null) {\\n                if (slotEl.className.indexOf(slotClassName) !== -1) {\\n                    return slotEl;\\n                }\\n                slotEl = slotEl.parentElement;\\n            }\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n        function closeAll(params) {\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className = params.closeWrapEl.className.replace(' _active', ' _hidden');\\n            removeElemEvent(params.closeEl, 'click', onCloseClick);\\n            removeElemEvent(params.closeOverEl, 'click', hideClose);\\n            for (var i = 0; i < params.closeItemsEl.length; i++) {\\n                removeElemEvent(params.closeItemsEl[i], 'click', onCloseReasonClick);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        function onCloseReasonClick(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            var pix = pixels[e.currentTarget.getAttribute('data-reason')];\\n            if (pix) { sendPix(pix, params); }\\n            sendPix(params.closeEl.getAttribute('data-closepix'), params);\\n            closeAll(params);\\n            \\/* dispatch close event to RbExt *\\/\\n            var parentBannerSlotItem = getParentBannerSlot(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            if (parentBannerSlotItem) {\\n                dispatchEvent(parentBannerSlotItem, 'mrg-close');\\n            }\\n        }\\n        function onCloseClick(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            if <script>
	var xray = {
		send: function (t, data) {
			var src = '//xray.mail.ru/update?p=light&t=' + encodeURIComponent(t);

			if (data) {
				var iItems = data.i;
				if (iItems) {
					if (typeof iItems === 'string') {
						iItems = [iItems];
					}

					var iItemsParts = [];

					if (Object.prototype.toString.call(iItems) === '[object Array]') {
						for (var i = iItems.length; i--;) {
							iItemsParts.push(encodeURIComponent(iItems[i]) + ':1');
						}
					} else {
						for (var key in iItems) {
							iItemsParts.push(encodeURIComponent(key) + ':' + encodeURIComponent(iItems[key]));
						}
					}

					src += '&i=' + iItemsParts.join(',');
				}

				try {
					if (data.rlog_message) {
						src += '&rlog_message=' + encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(data.rlog_message));
					}

					if (data.rlog) {
						src += '&rlog=' + encodeURIComponent(data.rlog);
					}
				} catch (e) {
				}
			}

			src += '&v=1&email=test_nt_1@mail.ru&rnd=' + Math.random();

			(new Image()).src = src;
		}
	};
</script>

<script>
	(function (w, d) {
		var close = d.getElementById('announcements__needmodernbrowser__infomessage__close');
		close.onclick = function () {
			try {
				m$portal.cookie('browser_warning_hide', 1, {expires: 365, path: '/'});
			} catch (e) {
			}

			new Image().src = '//rs.mail.ru/sb3950567.gif?' + Math.random();

			setTimeout(function () {
				location.reload();
			}, 100);

			xray.send('ann', {
				i: 'needmodernbrowser_close'
			});
		};
	})(window, document);
</script>

<script type="text/javascript">
	(function (w, d, ua) {
		try {
			var
				mail_cookie = m$portal.S_Cookie('mail')
				, blocks = {
					'allowed-full-version': {
						el: d.getElementById('announcements__allowed-full-version')
					}
					, 'needmodernbrowser': {
						el: d.getElementById('announcements__needmodernbrowser')
						, closed: m$portal.cookie('browser_warning_hide')
					}
					, 'compatibility-mode': {
						el: d.getElementById('announcements__compatibility-mode')
						, closed: m$portal.cookie('browser_iecm_hide')
					}
				}
				, can_use_full_version = true
				, compatibility_mode = /\bMSIE\s[67]/.test(ua) && /\bTrident/.test(ua)
				, light = mail_cookie.getLocal('light')
			;

			

			if (light) {
				if (can_use_full_version) {
					blocks['allowed-full-version'].el.style.display = '';
					new Image().src = '//rs.mail.ru/d3950576.gif?' + Math.random();
					new Image().src = '//mail.radar.imgsmail.ru/update?email=test_nt_1@mail.ru&p=mail&t=lite_afv_an&v=1&rlog=lite_afv_an&rlog_message=' + encodeURIComponent('ua=' + ua) + '&rnd=' + Math.random();

					xray.send('ann', {
						i: 'allowed-full-version'
					});
				} else {
					if (compatibility_mode) {
						if (!blocks['compatibility-mode'].closed) {
							blocks['compatibility-mode'].el.style.display = '';
							new Image().src = '//rs.mail.ru/d5825351.gif?' + Math.random();

							xray.send('ann', {
								i: 'compatibility-mode'
							});
						}
					} else {
						if (!blocks['needmodernbrowser'].closed) {
							blocks['needmodernbrowser'].el.style.display = '';
							new Image().src = '//rs.mail.ru/d3950567.gif?' + Math.random();

							xray.send('ann', {
								i: 'needmodernbrowser'
							});
						}
					}
				}
			}
		} catch (e) {
		}
	})(window, document, navigator.userAgent);
</script>

<script type="text/javascript" >
try {
    (function(global, name, url) {
        url = url || '//r3.mail.ru/j/';
        var yaads = global[name] || [];
        global.yaads_rb_logs = global.yaads_rb_logs || {};
        function get_charmap() {
            var exceptions = [34, 35, 37, 47, 60, 62, 63, 75, 91, 92, 93, 94, 96, 107, 123, 124, 125];
            var charmap = {
                46: 33, //. => !
                45: 36, //- => $
                32: 40 //  => (
            }
            var fbc = [38, 39, 43, 61, 126];
            /*["&", "'", "+", "=", "~"] - some browsers uses percent-encoding for this symbols, but we stil can use it in charmap for any rare thing. NB! ~ (126) is used as field separator*/

            var not_avaliable = exceptions.concat(fbc);
            for (var k in charmap) {
                not_avaliable.push(charmap[k]);
            }

            var code = 33;

            function get_code() {
                while (code < 127 && not_avaliable.indexOf(code) >= 0) {
                    code += 1;
                }
                return code++;
            }

            var ranges = [
                [48, 58], // - digits
                [97, 123], // - latin
                [1072, 1104], // - russian
                [1105, 1106] // russian "—ë"
            ];

            for (var i = 0; i < ranges.length; i++) {
                var s = ranges[i][0],
                    f = ranges[i][1];
                while (s < f) {
                    charmap[s] = get_code();
                    if (!charmap[s]) throw new Error('can\'t encode character ' + String.fromCharCode(s) + '(' + s + ')');
                    s++;
                }
            }
            return charmap;
        }
        function encodeStr(str, charmap) {
            var unknown = 32;
            var replacements = [
                [/\s/g, ' ']
            ];
            str = str.toLowerCase();
            for (var i = 0; i < replacements.length; i++) {
                str = str.replace.apply(str, replacements[i]);
            }
            var coded = [];
            for (var i = 0, l = str.length; i < l; i++) {
                var c = str.charCodeAt(i);
                c = charmap[c] ? charmap[c] : charmap[unknown];
                coded[i] = String.fromCharCode(c);
            }
            return coded.join('');
        }
        function getUrlLogItem(data) {
            var charmap = get_charmap();
            var title = data.assets.filter(function(ob) {
                return ob.title;
            }).pop();
            title = title && title.title && title.title.value || '';
            var text = data.assets.filter(function(ob) {
                return ob.data && ob.ext && ob.ext.type === 2;
            }).pop();
            text = text && text.data && text.data.value || '';
            var domain = data.assets.filter(function(ob) {
                return ob.data && ob.ext && ob.ext.type === 11;
            }).pop();
            domain = domain && domain.data.value || '';
            if (!title || !text || !domain) {
                return '';
            }
            return [encodeStr(domain, charmap), encodeStr(title, charmap), encodeStr(text, charmap)].join(String.fromCharCode('126'));
        }
        function setLogs(data, newAdIds) {
            var adItems = [];
            for (var a = 0; a < data.adIds.length; a++) {
                if (newAdIds.indexOf(data.adIds[a]) !== -1) {
                    adItems.push(data.bid[a]);
                }
            }
            var bound = (2083 - url.length);
            var l = 0;
            var ind = 0;
            var ads = [];
            while (ind < adItems.length && l < bound) {
                var adItem = adItems[ind];
                var itemData = adItem.adm.native;
                /*if (!!itemData.adType || adItems.length === 1) {*/
                    // —É –µ–¥–∏–Ω—Å—Ç–≤–µ–Ω–Ω–æ–≥–æ –≤ –º–∞—Å—Å–∏–≤–µ –Ω–µ—Ç adType, –Ω–æ —É–∂–µ –æ—Ç—Å–µ—è–ª–∏ –≤—ã—à–µ –ø–æ adIds
                    var str = getUrlLogItem(itemData);

                    l += str.length;
                    if (l > bound) break;
                    if (!!str) {
                        ads.push(str);
                    }
                /*}*/
                ind++;
            }
            // console.log(url + ads.join('/'));
            new Image().src = url + ads.join('/');
        }

        Object.defineProperty(window, 'yaads', {
            get: function() { return yaads; },
            set: function(newYaads) {
                if (newYaads.callSuccessCb) {
                    var oldCS = newYaads.callSuccessCb;
                    newYaads.callSuccessCb = function(t) {
                        // console.log('Render data', t);
                        var seatbidData = t.data.seatbid;
                        var idInLogs = global.yaads_rb_logs.hasOwnProperty(t.id);
                        var globalItemadIds = idInLogs ? global.yaads_rb_logs[t.id].adIds : [];
                        var newAdsIds = [];
                        var adIds = seatbidData[0].adIds;
                        if (adIds && adIds.length) {
                            for (var arrInd = 0; arrInd < adIds.length; arrInd++) {
                                if (globalItemadIds.indexOf(adIds[arrInd]) === -1) {
                                    newAdsIds.push(adIds[arrInd]);
                                }
                            }
                        }

                        if (!!newAdsIds.length) {
                            setLogs(seatbidData[0], newAdsIds);
                            if (!idInLogs) {
                                global.yaads_rb_logs[t.id] = {};
                            }
                            global.yaads_rb_logs[t.id]['id'] = t.id;
                            global.yaads_rb_logs[t.id]['adIds'] = globalItemadIds.concat(newAdsIds);
                        }
                        oldCS.call(newYaads, t);
                    }
                }
                yaads = newYaads;
                // console.log('Try set yaads:', newYaads)
            },
            enumerable: true,
            configurable: true
        });
    })(this, "yaads");

} catch (e) {
    try {
        // console.log('//r3.mail.ru/j/error/' + e.message);
        new Image().src = '//r3.mail.ru/j/error/?t=' + new Date().getTime() + '&e=' + encodeURIComponent(e.name) + '&m=' + encodeURIComponent(e.message)
    } catch (e) {}
}
</script>

<script>
	var xray = {
		send: function (t, data) {
			var src = '//xray.mail.ru/update?p=light&t=' + encodeURIComponent(t);

			if (data) {
				var iItems = data.i;
				if (iItems) {
					if (typeof iItems === 'string') {
						iItems = [iItems];
					}

					var iItemsParts = [];

					if (Object.prototype.toString.call(iItems) === '[object Array]') {
						for (var i = iItems.length; i--;) {
							iItemsParts.push(encodeURIComponent(iItems[i]) + ':1');
						}
					} else {
						for (var key in iItems) {
							iItemsParts.push(encodeURIComponent(key) + ':' + encodeURIComponent(iItems[key]));
						}
					}

					src += '&i=' + iItemsParts.join(',');
				}

				try {
					if (data.rlog_message) {
						src += '&rlog_message=' + encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(data.rlog_message));
					}

					if (data.rlog) {
						src += '&rlog=' + encodeURIComponent(data.rlog);
					}
				} catch (e) {
				}
			}

			src += '&v=1&email=test_nt_1@mail.ru&rnd=' + Math.random();

			(new Image()).src = src;
		}
	};
</script>

<img src="//an.mail.ru/count/U_4amautHtK505u0488WCPTsrL400000O9WBSFJqW908a042m042s06AXnte0O01y0ACkfAo1h030g06gWF91hi-4Mkr5qq5gGU6her73VSAJj070l8D0FeD088E0000" style="width:0;height:0;position:absolute;visibility:hidden;" alt="" />




<script type="text/javascript" >
try {
    (function(global, name, url) {
        url = url || '//r3.mail.ru/j/';
        var yaads = global[name] || [];
        global.yaads_rb_logs = global.yaads_rb_logs || {};
        function get_charmap() {
            var exceptions = [34, 35, 37, 47, 60, 62, 63, 75, 91, 92, 93, 94, 96, 107, 123, 124, 125];
            var charmap = {
                46: 33, //. => !
                45: 36, //- => $
                32: 40 //  => (
            }
            var fbc = [38, 39, 43, 61, 126];
            /*["&", "'", "+", "=", "~"] - some browsers uses percent-encoding for this symbols, but we stil can use it in charmap for any rare thing. NB! ~ (126) is used as field separator*/

            var not_avaliable = exceptions.concat(fbc);
            for (var k in charmap) {
                not_avaliable.push(charmap[k]);
            }

            var code = 33;

            function get_code() {
                while (code < 127 && not_avaliable.indexOf(code) >= 0) {
                    code += 1;
                }
                return code++;
            }

            var ranges = [
                [48, 58], // - digits
                [97, 123], // - latin
                [1072, 1104], // - russian
                [1105, 1106] // russian "—ë"
            ];

            for (var i = 0; i < ranges.length; i++) {
                var s = ranges[i][0],
                    f = ranges[i][1];
                while (s < f) {
                    charmap[s] = get_code();
                    if (!charmap[s]) throw new Error('can\'t encode character ' + String.fromCharCode(s) + '(' + s + ')');
                    s++;
                }
            }
            return charmap;
        }
        function encodeStr(str, charmap) {
            var unknown = 32;
            var replacements = [
                [/\s/g, ' ']
            ];
            str = str.toLowerCase();
            for (var i = 0; i < replacements.length; i++) {
                str = str.replace.apply(str, replacements[i]);
            }
            var coded = [];
            for (var i = 0, l = str.length; i < l; i++) {
                var c = str.charCodeAt(i);
                c = charmap[c] ? charmap[c] : charmap[unknown];
                coded[i] = String.fromCharCode(c);
            }
            return coded.join('');
        }
        function getUrlLogItem(data) {
            var charmap = get_charmap();
            var title = data.assets.filter(function(ob) {
                return ob.title;
            }).pop();
            title = title && title.title && title.title.value || '';
            var text = data.assets.filter(function(ob) {
                return ob.data && ob.ext && ob.ext.type === 2;
            }).pop();
            text = text && text.data && text.data.value || '';
            var domain = data.assets.filter(function(ob) {
                return ob.data && ob.ext && ob.ext.type === 11;
            }).pop();
            domain = domain && domain.data.value || '';
            if (!title || !text || !domain) {
                return '';
            }
            return [encodeStr(domain, charmap), encodeStr(title, charmap), encodeStr(text, charmap)].join(String.fromCharCode('126'));
        }
        function setLogs(data, newAdIds) {
            var adItems = [];
            for (var a = 0; a < data.adIds.length; a++) {
                if (newAdIds.indexOf(data.adIds[a]) !== -1) {
                    adItems.push(data.bid[a]);
                }
            }
            var bound = (2083 - url.length);
            var l = 0;
            var ind = 0;
            var ads = [];
            while (ind < adItems.length && l < bound) {
                var adItem = adItems[ind];
                var itemData = adItem.adm.native;
                /*if (!!itemData.adType || adItems.length === 1) {*/
                    // —É –µ–¥–∏–Ω—Å—Ç–≤–µ–Ω–Ω–æ–≥–æ –≤ –º–∞—Å—Å–∏–≤–µ –Ω–µ—Ç adType, –Ω–æ —É–∂–µ –æ—Ç—Å–µ—è–ª–∏ –≤—ã—à–µ –ø–æ adIds
                    var str = getUrlLogItem(itemData);

                    l += str.length;
                    if (l > bound) break;
                    if (!!str) {
                        ads.push(str);
                    }
                /*}*/
                ind++;
            }
            // console.log(url + ads.join('/'));
            new Image().src = url + ads.join('/');
        }

        Object.defineProperty(window, 'yaads', {
            get: function() { return yaads; },
            set: function(newYaads) {
                if (newYaads.callSuccessCb) {
                    var oldCS = newYaads.callSuccessCb;
                    newYaads.callSuccessCb = function(t) {
                        // console.log('Render data', t);
                        var seatbidData = t.data.seatbid;
                        var idInLogs = global.yaads_rb_logs.hasOwnProperty(t.id);
                        var globalItemadIds = idInLogs ? global.yaads_rb_logs[t.id].adIds : [];
                        var newAdsIds = [];
                        var adIds = seatbidData[0].adIds;
                        if (adIds && adIds.length) {
                            for (var arrInd = 0; arrInd < adIds.length; arrInd++) {
                                if (globalItemadIds.indexOf(adIds[arrInd]) === -1) {
                                    newAdsIds.push(adIds[arrInd]);
                                }
                            }
                        }

                        if (!!newAdsIds.length) {
                            setLogs(seatbidData[0], newAdsIds);
                            if (!idInLogs) {
                                global.yaads_rb_logs[t.id] = {};
                            }
                            global.yaads_rb_logs[t.id]['id'] = t.id;
                            global.yaads_rb_logs[t.id]['adIds'] = globalItemadIds.concat(newAdsIds);
                        }
                        oldCS.call(newYaads, t);
                    }
                }
                yaads = newYaads;
                // console.log('Try set yaads:', newYaads)
            },
            enumerable: true,
            configurable: true
        });
    })(this, "yaads");

} catch (e) {
    try {
        // console.log('//r3.mail.ru/j/error/' + e.message);
        new Image().src = '//r3.mail.ru/j/error/?t=' + new Date().getTime() + '&e=' + encodeURIComponent(e.name) + '&m=' + encodeURIComponent(e.message)
    } catch (e) {}
}
</script>

}\\n<\\/style>\\n    <script>\\n    (function(params) {\\n        var closeEl, closeBubbleEl, closeItemsEl, closeWrapEl, closeOverEl;\\n        var pixels = {\\n            ni: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635784.gif?\\",\\n            ab: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635789.gif?\\",\\n            sp: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635790.gif?\\",\\n            cv: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635791.gif?\\"\\n        };\\n        function stopE(e) {\\n            if (e) { e.preventDefault(); e.stopImmediatePropagation(); }\\n        }\\n        function addElemEvent(E, eventName, callback) {\\n            E.addEventListener ? E.addEventListener(eventName, callback, !1) : E.attachEvent && E.attachEvent(\\"on\\" + eventName, callback);\\n        }\\n        function removeElemEvent(E, eventName, callback) {\\n            E.removeEventListener ? E.removeEventListener(eventName, callback, !1) : E.detachEvent && E.detachEvent(\\"on\\" + eventName, callback);\\n        }\\n        function dispatchEvent(el, type) {\\n            var evt;\\n            if (typeof window.CustomEvent === 'function') {\\n                evt = new CustomEvent(type, {\\n                    bubbles: true\\n                });\\n            } else {\\n                evt = document.createEvent('CustomEvent');\\n                evt.initCustomEvent(type, true, false, null);\\n            }\\n            el.dispatchEvent(evt);\\n        }\\n        function sendPix(pix, params) {\\n            var img = document.createElement('img');\\n            img.src = pix || '';\\n            img.style.display = 'none';\\n            params.closeWrapEl.appendChild(img);\\n        }\\n        function getParentBannerItem(el) {\\n            var retval = null;\\n            var parentAttr = 'data-closewrap-container';\\n            var parentEl = el;\\n            while (parentEl) {\\n                if (parentEl === document.getElementsByTagName('body')[0]) {\\n                    retval = null;\\n                    break;\\n                } else if (parentEl.getAttribute(parentAttr)) {\\n                    retval = parentEl;\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n                parentEl = parentEl.parentElement;\\n            }\\n            return retval;\\n        }\\n        function getParentBannerSlot(el) {\\n            var slotClassName = 'mrg-tag';\\n            var slotEl = el;\\n            if (typeof el.closest === 'function') {\\n                return el.closest('.' + slotClassName);\\n            }\\n            while (slotEl !== null) {\\n                if (slotEl.className.indexOf(slotClassName) !== -1) {\\n                    return slotEl;\\n                }\\n                slotEl = slotEl.parentElement;\\n            }\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n        function closeAll(params) {\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className = params.closeWrapEl.className.replace(' _active', ' _hidden');\\n            removeElemEvent(params.closeEl, 'click', onCloseClick);\\n            removeElemEvent(params.closeOverEl, 'click', hideClose);\\n            for (var i = 0; i < params.closeItemsEl.length; i++) {\\n                removeElemEvent(params.closeItemsEl[i], 'click', onCloseReasonClick);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        function onCloseReasonClick(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            var pix = pixels[e.currentTarget.getAttribute('data-reason')];\\n            if (pix) { sendPix(pix, params); }\\n            sendPix(params.closeEl.getAttribute('data-closepix'), params);\\n            closeAll(params);\\n            \\/* dispatch close event to RbExt *\\/\\n            var parentBannerSlotItem = getParentBannerSlot(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            if (parentBannerSlotItem) {\\n                dispatchEvent(parentBannerSlotItem, 'mrg-close');\\n            }\\n        }\\n        function onCloseClick(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            if (params.closeWrapEl.className.indexOf(' _active') === -1) { showClose(params); } else { hideClose(params); }\\n        }\\n        function hideClose(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className = params.closeWrapEl.className.replace(' _active', '');\\n            var parentBannerWrapItem = getParentBannerItem(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            parentBannerWrapItem.className = parentBannerWrapItem.className.replace(' _close-overlay', '');\\n        }\\n        function showClose(params) {\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className += ' _active';\\n            var parentBannerWrapItem = getParentBannerItem(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            parentBannerWrapItem.className += ' _close-overlay';\\n        }\\n        function init() {\\n            if (!params || !params.rootId || !document.querySelectorAll) return;\\n            var rootElem = document.getElementById(params.rootId);\\n            if (!rootElem) return;\\n            closeWrapEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-cross-wrap');\\n            if (!closeWrapEl || !closeWrapEl[0]) return;\\n            closeEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-cross');\\n            closeBubbleEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-cross-bubble');\\n            closeOverEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-overlay');\\n            for (var k = 0; k < closeEl.length; k++) {\\n                closeItemsEl = closeWrapEl[k].querySelectorAll('.js-close-reason');\\n                if (!closeEl || !closeBubbleEl || !closeOverEl || !closeWrapEl[k] || E.addEventListener(eventName, callback, !1) : E.attachEvent && E.attachEvent(\\"on\\" + eventName, callback);\\n        }\\n        function removeElemEvent(E, eventName, callback) {\\n            E.removeEventListener ?       if (typeof window.CustomEvent === 'function') {\\n                evt = new CustomEvent(type, {\\n                    bubbles: true\\n                });\\n            } else {\\n params.closeWrapEl.appendChild(img);\\n        }\\n        function getParentBannerItem(el) {\\n            var retval = null;\\n            var parentAttr = 'data-closewrap-container';\\n            var parentEl = el;\\n            while (parentEl) {\\n                if (parentEl === document.getElementsByTagName('body')[0]) {\\n                    retval = null;\\n                    break;\\n                } else if (parentEl.getAttribute(parentAttr)) {\\n                    retval = parentEl;\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n                parentEl = parentEl.parentElement;\\n            }\\n            return retval;\\n        }\\n        function getParentBannerSlot(el) {\\n            var slotClassName = 'mrg-tag';\\n            var slotEl = (slotEl.className.indexOf(slotClassName) !== -1) {\\n                    return slotEl;\\n                }\\n                slotEl = slotEl.parentElement;\\n            }\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n        function closeAll(params) {\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className = params.closeWrapEl.className.replace(' _active', ' _hidden');\\n              removeElemEvent(params.closeItemsEl[i], 'click', onCloseReasonClick);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        function onCloseReasonClick(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n (params.closeWrapEl.className.indexOf(' _active') === -1) { showClose(params); } else { hideClose(params); }\\n        }\\n        function hideClose(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n }\\n<\\/style>\\n    <script>\\n    (function(params) {\\n        var closeEl, closeBubbleEl, closeItemsEl, closeWrapEl, closeOverEl;\\n        var pixels = {\\n            ni: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635784.gif?\\",\\n            ab: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635789.gif?\\",\\n            sp: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635790.gif?\\",\\n            cv: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635791.gif?\\"\\n        };\\n        function stopE(e) {\\n            if (e) { e.preventDefault(); e.stopImmediatePropagation(); }\\n        }\\n        function addElemEvent(E, eventName, callback) {\\n            E.addEventListener ? E.addEventListener(eventName, callback, !1) : E.attachEvent && E.attachEvent(\\"on\\" + eventName, callback);\\n        }\\n        function removeElemEvent(E, eventName, callback) {\\n            E.removeEventListener ? E.removeEventListener(eventName, callback, !1) : E.detachEvent && E.detachEvent(\\"on\\" + eventName, callback);\\n        }\\n        function dispatchEvent(el, type) {\\n            var evt;\\n            if (typeof window.CustomEvent === 'function') {\\n                evt = new CustomEvent(type, {\\n                    bubbles: true\\n                });\\n            } else {\\n                evt = document.createEvent('CustomEvent');\\n                evt.initCustomEvent(type, true, false, null);\\n            }\\n            el.dispatchEvent(evt);\\n        }\\n        function sendPix(pix, params) {\\n            var img = document.createElement('img');\\n            img.src = pix || '';\\n            img.style.display = 'none';\\n            params.closeWrapEl.appendChild(img);\\n        }\\n        function getParentBannerItem(el) {\\n            var retval = null;\\n            var parentAttr = 'data-closewrap-container';\\n            var parentEl = el;\\n            while (parentEl) {\\n                if (parentEl === document.getElementsByTagName('body')[0]) {\\n                    retval = null;\\n                    break;\\n                } else if (parentEl.getAttribute(parentAttr)) {\\n                    retval = parentEl;\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n                parentEl = parentEl.parentElement;\\n            }\\n            return retval;\\n        }\\n        function getParentBannerSlot(el) {\\n            var slotClassName = 'mrg-tag';\\n            var slotEl = el;\\n            if (typeof el.closest === 'function') {\\n                return el.closest('.' + slotClassName);\\n            }\\n            while (slotEl !== null) {\\n                if (slotEl.className.indexOf(slotClassName) !== -1) {\\n                    return slotEl;\\n                }\\n                slotEl = slotEl.parentElement;\\n            }\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n        function closeAll(params) {\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className = params.closeWrapEl.className.replace(' _active', ' _hidden');\\n            removeElemEvent(params.closeEl, 'click', onCloseClick);\\n            removeElemEvent(params.closeOverEl, 'click', hideClose);\\n            for (var i = 0; i < params.closeItemsEl.length; i++) {\\n                removeElemEvent(params.closeItemsEl[i], 'click', onCloseReasonClick);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        function onCloseReasonClick(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            var pix = pixels[e.currentTarget.getAttribute('data-reason')];\\n            if (pix) { sendPix(pix, params); }\\n            sendPix(params.closeEl.getAttribute('data-closepix'), params);\\n            closeAll(params);\\n            \\/* dispatch close event to RbExt *\\/\\n            var parentBannerSlotItem = getParentBannerSlot(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            if (parentBannerSlotItem) {\\n                dispatchEvent(parentBannerSlotItem, 'mrg-close');\\n            }\\n        }\\n        function onCloseClick(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            if (params.closeWrapEl.className.indexOf(' _active') === -1) { showClose(params); } else { hideClose(params); }\\n        }\\n        function hideClose(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className = params.closeWrapEl.className.replace(' _active', '');\\n            var parentBannerWrapItem = getParentBannerItem(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            parentBannerWrapItem.className = parentBannerWrapItem.className.replace(' _close-overlay', '');\\n        }\\n        function showClose(params) {\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className += ' _active';\\n            var parentBannerWrapItem = getParentBannerItem(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            parentBannerWrapItem.className += ' _close-overlay';\\n        }\\n        function init() {\\n            if (!params || !params.rootId || !document.querySelectorAll) return;\\n            var rootElem = document.getElementById(params.rootId);\\n            if (!rootElem) return;\\n            closeWrapEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-cross-wrap');\\n            if (!closeWrapEl || !closeWrapEl[0]) return;\\n            closeEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-cross');\\n            closeBubbleEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-cross-bubble');\\n            closeOverEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-overlay');\\n            for (var k = 0; k < closeEl.length; k++) {\\n                closeItemsEl = closeWrapEl[k].querySelectorAll('.js-close-reason');\\n                if (!closeEl || !closeBubbleEl || !closeOverEl || !closeWrapEl[k] || !closeEl[k] || !closeBubbleEl[k] || !closeOverEl[k]) return;\\n                addElemEvent(closeBubbleEl[k], 'click', function(e) {\\n                    e.stopImmediatePropagation();\\n                    e.preventDefault();\\n                });\\n                addElemEvent(closeEl[k], 'click', onCloseClick.bind(null, {\\n                    closeWrapEl:closeWrapEl[k],\\n                    closeEl:closeEl[k],\\n                    closeBubbleEl:closeBubbleEl[k],\\n                    closeOverEl:closeOverEl[k],\\n                    closeItemsEl:closeItemsEl\\n                }));\\n                addElemEvent(closeOverEl[k], 'click', hideClose.bind(null, {\\n                    closeWrapEl:closeWrapEl[k],\\n                    closeEl:closeEl[k],\\n                    closeBubbleEl:closeBubbleEl[k],\\n                    closeOverEl:closeOverEl[k],\\n                    closeItemsEl:closeItemsEl\\n                }));\\n                for (var i = 0; i < closeItemsEl.length; i++) {\\n                    addElemEvent(closeItemsEl[i], 'click', onCloseReasonClick.bind(null, {\\n                        closeWrapEl:closeWrapEl[k],\\n                        closeEl:closeEl[k],\\n                        closeBubbleEl:closeBubbleEl[k],\\n                        closeOverEl:closeOverEl[k],\\n                        closeItemsEl:closeItemsEl\\n                    }));\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        init();\\n    })({rootId: 'b53098971_1975275955'});\\n<\\/script>\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n            ni: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635784.gif?\\",\\n            ab: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635789.gif?\\",\\n            sp: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635790.gif?\\",\\n            cv: \\"https:\\/\\/rs.mail.ru\\/sb36635791.gif?\\"\\n        };\\n        function stopE(e) {\\n            if (e) { e.preventDefault(); e.stopImmediatePropagation(); }\\n        }\\n        function addElemEvent(E, eventName, callback) {\\n            E.addEventListener ? E.addEventListener(eventName, callback, !1) : E.attachEvent && E.attachEvent(\\"on\\" + eventName, callback);\\n        }\\n        function removeElemEvent(E, eventName, callback) {\\n            E.removeEventListener ? E.removeEventListener(eventName, callback, !1) : E.detachEvent && E.detachEvent(\\"on\\" + eventName, callback);\\n        }\\n        function dispatchEvent(el, type) {\\n            var evt;\\n            if (typeof window.CustomEvent === 'function') {\\n                evt = new CustomEvent(type, {\\n                    bubbles: true\\n                });\\n            } else {\\n                evt = document.createEvent('CustomEvent');\\n                evt.initCustomEvent(type, true, false, null);\\n            }\\n            el.dispatchEvent(evt);\\n        }\\n        function sendPix(pix, params) {\\n            var img = document.createElement('img');\\n            img.src = pix || '';\\n            img.style.display = 'none';\\n            params.closeWrapEl.appendChild(img);\\n        }\\n        function getParentBannerItem(el) {\\n            var retval = null;\\n            var parentAttr = 'data-closewrap-container';\\n            var parentEl = el;\\n            while (parentEl) {\\n                if (parentEl === document.getElementsByTagName('body')[0]) {\\n                    retval = null;\\n                    break;\\n                } else if (parentEl.getAttribute(parentAttr)) {\\n                    retval = parentEl;\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n                parentEl = parentEl.parentElement;\\n            }\\n            return retval;\\n        }\\n        function getParentBannerSlot(el) {\\n            var slotClassName = 'mrg-tag';\\n            var slotEl = el;\\n            if (typeof el.closest === 'function') {\\n                return el.closest('.' + slotClassName);\\n            }\\n            while (slotEl !== null) {\\n                if (slotEl.className.indexOf(slotClassName) !== -1) {\\n                    return slotEl;\\n                }\\n                slotEl = slotEl.parentElement;\\n            }\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n        function closeAll(params) {\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className = params.closeWrapEl.className.replace(' _active', ' _hidden');\\n            removeElemEvent(params.closeEl, 'click', onCloseClick);\\n            removeElemEvent(params.closeOverEl, 'click', hideClose);\\n            for (var i = 0; i < params.closeItemsEl.length; i++) {\\n                removeElemEvent(params.closeItemsEl[i], 'click', onCloseReasonClick);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        function onCloseReasonClick(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            var pix = pixels[e.currentTarget.getAttribute('data-reason')];\\n            if (pix) { sendPix(pix, params); }\\n            sendPix(params.closeEl.getAttribute('data-closepix'), params);\\n            closeAll(params);\\n            \\/* dispatch close event to RbExt *\\/\\n            var parentBannerSlotItem = getParentBannerSlot(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            if (parentBannerSlotItem) {\\n                dispatchEvent(parentBannerSlotItem, 'mrg-close');\\n            }\\n        }\\n        function onCloseClick(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            if (params.closeWrapEl.className.indexOf(' _active') === -1) { showClose(params); } else { hideClose(params); }\\n        }\\n        function hideClose(params, e) {\\n            stopE(e);\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className = params.closeWrapEl.className.replace(' _active', '');\\n            var parentBannerWrapItem = getParentBannerItem(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            parentBannerWrapItem.className = parentBannerWrapItem.className.replace(' _close-overlay', '');\\n        }\\n        function showClose(params) {\\n            params.closeWrapEl.className += ' _active';\\n            var parentBannerWrapItem = getParentBannerItem(params.closeWrapEl);\\n            parentBannerWrapItem.className += ' _close-overlay';\\n        }\\n        function init() {\\n            if (!params || !params.rootId || !document.querySelectorAll) return;\\n            var rootElem = document.getElementById(params.rootId);\\n            if (!rootElem) return;\\n            closeWrapEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-cross-wrap');\\n            if (!closeWrapEl || !closeWrapEl[0]) return;\\n            closeEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-cross');\\n            closeBubbleEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-cross-bubble');\\n            closeOverEl = rootElem.querySelectorAll('.js-close-overlay');\\n            for (var k = 0; k < closeEl.length; k++) {\\n                closeItemsEl = closeWrapEl[k].querySelectorAll('.js-close-reason');\\n                if (!closeEl || !closeBubbleEl || !closeOverEl || !closeWrapEl[k] || !closeEl[k] || !closeBubbleEl[k] || !closeOverEl[k]) return;\\n                addElemEvent(closeBubbleEl[k], 'click', function(e) {\\n                    e.stopImmediatePropagation();\\n                    e.preventDefault();\\n                });\\n                addElemEvent(closeEl[k], 'click', onCloseClick.bind(null, {\\n                    closeWrapEl:closeWrapEl[k],\\n                    closeEl:closeEl[k],\\n                    closeBubbleEl:closeBubbleEl[k],\\n                    closeOverEl:closeOverEl[k],\\n                    closeItemsEl:closeItemsEl\\n                }));\\n                addElemEvent(closeOverEl[k], 'click', hideClose.bind(null, {\\n                    closeWrapEl:closeWrapEl[k],\\n                    closeEl:closeEl[k],\\n                    closeBubbleEl:closeBubbleEl[k],\\n                    closeOverEl:closeOverEl[k],\\n                    closeItemsEl:closeItemsEl\\n                }));\\n                for (var i = 0; i < closeItemsEl.length; i++) {\\n                    addElemEvent(closeItemsEl[i], 'click', onCloseReasonClick.bind(null, {\\n                        closeWrapEl:closeWrapEl[k],\\n                        closeEl:closeEl[k],\\n                        closeBubbleEl:closeBubbleEl[k],\\n                        closeOverEl:closeOverEl[k],\\n                        closeItemsEl:closeItemsEl\\n                    }));\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        init();\\n    })({rootId: 'b72769268_2062862948'});\\n<\\/script>\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n
